I"•%<h1 class="no_toc" id="access-token">Access Token</h1>
<p class="fs-6 fw-300">The access token is a long random string that uniquely identifies a Pioneer within an app. The Access Token is the identifier that Applications use to communicate with the Pi Servers about a Pioneer. The Access Token is designed to protect the Pioneerâ€™s information from unapproved access. This page assumes that youâ€™ve read the <a href="../../gettingStarted/PiAppPlatform/piAppPlatformSDK">Pi SDK</a> page and have an understanding of how the Pi SDK and the Authenticate function work.</p>

<h2 class="no_toc text-delta" id="table-of-contents">Table of contents</h2>

